I'm not sure what the best fix is.

You could add something like 

``` js
if (typeof context.Object !== 'function') context = this;
```

You can customize the [IIFE](http://benalman.com/news/2010/11/immediately-invoked-function-expression/) around Lo-Dash via `lodash iife=...`.
See more on [custom builds](http://lodash.com/#custom-builds).

Can you change the default npm version to work with browserify?

I'd like to keep all of my dependencies on npm.
I can mod Lo-Dash to get its default global object elsewhere.

Thanks!

Any idea when that would be released on npm?
Not for at least another 2 weeks. This update cycle will include AMD/CommonJS module breakouts and other build tweaks.
OK; thanks!

As a general note, I think it's super cool how customizable Lo-Dash's builds are, but I especially appreciate the commitment @jdalton has shown to keeping the "default" distributions (on npm and elsewhere) as sensible as possible, supporting common use cases like AMD, browserify, etc.

+1 @jdalton’s dedication to Doing Things Right™ is an inspiration. <3
:heart:

I'm on 3.8.0 and am still seeing this issue. Am I doing something wrong or did it regress?

```
TypeError: Cannot read property 'prototype' of undefined
    at runInContext (cloud.js:15063:27)
    at Object.<anonymous> (cloud.js:26526:11)
    at Object.<anonymous> (cloud.js:26557:3)
    at Object.<anonymous> (cloud.js:26559:4)
    at s (cloud.js:1:220)
    at cloud.js:1:271
    at cloud.js:66750:5
```

And that line is

```
    var arrayProto = Array.prototype,
```

And in debugging a bit, that came from `var Array = root.Array` and `root` was set to `this`. `Array` is a valid global variable at this point, but `this.Array` doesn't work.

Hi @ptarjan!

It works for me. I need the deets.
A snippet and the commands you're using would help me to debug your issue.

Some more digging shows that `global.Object` is not defined by `browserify` in my context. 

(Some more context, I'm trying to push a browserified module to Parse.com's Cloud Code and during their push process I'm getting the error while lodash is trying to register itself).

If I remove all the `var Foo = context.Foo` things as well as just setting `nativeParseInt = parseInt` then it deploys.
A snippet and the commands you're using would help me to debug your issue.

Is this implemented yet?  I am facing the issue even on the latest version (3.10.1).
The patch suggested by @SLaks

``` js
if (typeof context.Object !== 'function') context = this;
```

 does the trick. 

Do you suggest going to the Browserify team to find a solution to this issue?

@jdalton the repro is very simple:

```
$ hombrew install v8 node

$ npm install -g browserify

$ npm install lodash

$ cat a.js
var _ = require('lodash');

$ browserify a.js > a.browserify.js

$ v8 a.browserify.js
a.browserify.js:720: TypeError: Cannot read property 'prototype' of undefined
    var arrayProto = Array.prototype,
                          ^
TypeError: Cannot read property 'prototype' of undefined
    at runInContext (a.browserify.js:720:27)
    at Object.<anonymous> (a.browserify.js:12322:11)
    at Object.<anonymous> (a.browserify.js:12353:3)
    at Object.1 (a.browserify.js:12355:4)
    at s (a.browserify.js:1:254)
    at a.browserify.js:1:305
    at Object.2.lodash (a.browserify.js:12357:9)
    at s (a.browserify.js:1:254)
    at e (a.browserify.js:1:425)
    at a.browserify.js:1:443
```

a.js:

``` js
var _ = require('lodash');
```

then

``` bash
browserify a.js > a.browserify.js
```

works.

@jdalton what does "works" mean? Are you running the output in `v8` (which doesn't expose the global variables the same way as nodeJS does)?

For reference, v8 runs lodash fine without the browserify transform:

```
$ v8 node_modules/lodash/index.js
```
Ah missed the `v8` bit. Hey, 4 months late is better than never :D
Sorry, I found a workaround so it didn't matter to me. One others piled on I cared more.
The issue is already resolved in master.
well then :ship: it
It'll go out with v4.0.
@magestican For v3 not so much. The issue is resolved in v4.
